<section class="faq-sec section-padding">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="center-data">
            <h2 class="fs-60">Common Questions</h2>
            <p>
                Find answers to the most common questions about our products,
                services, and policies. If you don’t see your question here,
                feel free to reach out to our team for more help.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-container">
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="grid-faq">
                    <div class="title-faq">
                        <h6 class="fs-30 p-0">
                            How often should I have my roof inspected?
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-icon">
                        <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bootm-data">
                    <p>
                        We recommend having your roof inspected at least once a
                        year, or immediately after a severe storm. Regular
                        inspections help catch minor issues before they become
                        costly leaks or structural damage.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="grid-faq">
                    <div class="title-faq">
                        <h6 class="fs-30 p-0">
                            What are the signs that I need new siding?
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-icon">
                        <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bootm-data">
                    <p>
                        Look out for cracks, warping, fading, or peeling paint.
                        If you notice drafts inside your home, visible rot, or a
                        sudden spike in energy bills, it might be time to
                        upgrade to new, energy-efficient siding.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="grid-faq">
                    <div class="title-faq">
                        <h6 class="fs-30 p-0">
                            How long does a typical roof replacement take?
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-icon">
                        <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bootm-data">
                    <p>
                        Most residential roof replacements can be completed in
                        just one to two days, depending on the size of your home
                        and weather conditions. Our team works efficiently to
                        minimize disruption to your daily life.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="grid-faq">
                    <div class="title-faq">
                        <h6 class="fs-30 p-0">
                            Do you offer warranties on your roofing and siding
                            work?
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-icon">
                        <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bootm-data">
                    <p>
                        Yes! We stand by the quality of our craftsmanship and
                        materials. We offer comprehensive manufacturer
                        warranties on all products, as well as a robust
                        workmanship guarantee for your complete peace of mind.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="grid-faq">
                    <div class="title-faq">
                        <h6 class="fs-30 p-0">
                            Can you install new siding over my existing
                            exterior?
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-icon">
                        <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bootm-data">
                    <p>
                        In some cases, new siding can be installed over existing
                        siding if the exterior is flat and in good condition.
                        However, a full tear-off is often recommended so we can
                        inspect and repair the underlying structure for moisture
                        damage.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="grid-faq">
                    <div class="title-faq">
                        <h6 class="fs-30 p-0">
                            Do you provide emergency roof repair services?
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-icon">
                        <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bootm-data">
                    <p>
                        Absolutely. We understand that severe storms, fallen
                        trees, and sudden leaks don't happen on a schedule. Our
                        team is available to safely tarp your roof and provide
                        prompt emergency repairs to protect your home.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    section.faq-sec {
        background: #ededed52;
    }

    /* FAQ CSS MAIN HERE  */
    .faq-section {
        max-width: 700px;
        margin: auto;
        background: #fff;
        padding: 25px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    .faq-item {
        border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        padding: 15px 0;
    }

    .faq-question {
        font-weight: 600;
        cursor: pointer;
        position: relative;
    }

    .faq-question::after {
        content: "+";
        position: absolute;
        right: 0;
        font-size: 18px;
        transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }

    .faq-item.active .faq-question::after {
        content: "−";
    }

    .faq-answer {
        display: none;
        margin-top: 10px;
        color: #444;
    }

    span.faq-symbol {
        height: 30px;
        width: 30px;
        background: var(--color-black);
        clip-path: polygon(
            45% 0%,
            55% 0%,
            55% 45%,
            100% 45%,
            100% 55%,
            55% 55%,
            55% 100%,
            45% 100%,
            45% 55%,
            0% 55%,
            0% 45%,
            45% 45%
        );
        display: block;
        transition: 0.3s ease-in;
    }

    .faq-icon {
        max-width: fit-content;
        width: 100%;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .grid-faq {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 10px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        cursor: pointer;
        background: var(--color-white);
    }

    .grid-faq,
    .bootm-data {
        padding: 15px 20px;
    }

    .bootm-data {
        display: none;
    }

    .faq-container {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 20px;
    }

    .grid-faq.active span.faq-symbol {
        transform: rotate(45deg);
    }

    .faq-holders .fs-30 {
        font-weight: 500;
    }

    /* FAQ CSS MAIN HERE END */
    @media (max-width: 1600px) {
        span.faq-symbol {
            height: 25px;
            width: 25px;
        }
    }
    @media (max-width: 767px) {
        span.faq-symbol {
            height: 20px;
            width: 20px;
        }
    }
</style>

<script>
    $(document).ready(function () {
        $(".grid-faq").click(function () {
            let $faqHolder = $(this).closest(".faq-holders"); // current faq-holder

            // Close all
            $(".faq-holders .bootm-data").slideUp();
            $(".grid-faq").removeClass("active");

            // Toggle current
            if (!$faqHolder.find(".bootm-data").is(":visible")) {
                $faqHolder.find(".bootm-data").slideDown();
                $(this).addClass("active");
            }
        });
    });
</script>
